You can check these events without leaving the AWS console. This is how findings reported by Sysdig CloudConnector look in the AWS Security Hub:
 Browse to Security Hub and click &lsquo;Findings&rsquo; on the left.   Click on &ldquo;Delete bucket encryption&rdquo; to view all the information you need to take immediate action:   And they appear in JSON format in AWS CloudWatch log streams.
Browse to CloudWatch, and click &lsquo;Log groups &gt; cloud-connector &gt; alerts&rsquo;

&lt;!&ndash; If you followed this workshop from the beginning then you should have deployed the CloudTrail CloudFormation Template earlier. If you didn&rsquo;t, then go back and complete this step now Setup CloudTrail Runtime Security, however please note that this can take up to ten minutes to complete.
To check it has been deployed successfully, navigate to https://console.aws.amazon.com/cloudformation/ and search for CloudConnector. You should see it&rsquo;s status is CREATE_COMPLETE.
